stu_tags: HILARIOUS  SKIP CLASS? YOU WON\'T PASS.
comments: Great prof, loved him! Hilarious and very intelligent. I did well on multiple choice by just doing the quizzes and flashcards on the online resource he gave. The short answers are based on additional articles and course content but they aren\'t worth that much and he explicitly tells you in class what to focus on. He is helpful if you seek help.

stu_tags: GET READY TO READ  LECTURE HEAVY  SO MANY PAPERS
comments: Dr. Fenske is a great guy. He\'s witty, energetic, and clearly loves what he does. His teaching style on the other hand is something else. Cognitive Neuroscience is not something that is easy to understand for everyone, yet this man just pours out all of the information in a torrential flow without stopping to let you absorb what was said.

comments: Very difficult and confusing class. He is a little condescending when he talks, but besides that he\'s not too bad. He is not very helpful when you ask questions, I asked him something once and he didn\'t answer it. Assignments are sometimes unclear, and he doesn\'t explain what\'s expected in them very well.

comments: This guy is hard to rate because he\'s stuck with the unfortunate task of teaching PSYC Intro Research Methods, which is both totally boring and mandatory. Considering this, I think he showed valiant effort to make the class as painless and as interesting as could have been reasonably expected by any prof. So really, points for effort!
